Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.30,0:03:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:234303,236180}Isabelle, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.51,0:03:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:236513,238098}Go ahead of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:239808,241143}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:245898,247441}Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.73,0:04:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:251737,253447}We're leaving, fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.45,0:04:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:263457,265083}Jean, we're ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.08,0:04:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:265083,266460}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:278096,280641}Isabelle, we've got to\Ndetach the chain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:288649,290150}All right, I'll row!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.86,0:04:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:291860,294863}You can do it, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.86,0:04:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:294863,296823}Faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.29,0:05:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:313298,315133}Do you think we can make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.13,0:05:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:315133,319471}So far, everything's worked out.\NIt'll be fine. Don't worry, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:320055,321723}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:327145,331400}{\i1}Meanwhile, in Versailles…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.10,0:05:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:332109,335320}Mr. Thiers, why\Ndid you flee Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:335779,340784}After losing the capital, our troops have lost\Ntheir morale and are in disarray now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.03,0:05:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:341034,345914}I would appreciate it if you did not\Nblame me for your own failures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.91,0:05:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:345914,349418}It is you who did not manage\Nto gather the army you promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:349418,351628}How do you intend\Nto take responsibility for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.96,0:05:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:351962,357009}Further conversation is pointless. I don't\Nwant to talk to a coward like you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.38,0:06:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:360387,363098}Are you resigning?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:363098,365142}I'm sorry to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.89,0:06:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:365892,367436}General Gambetta…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.44,0:06:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376445,381825}Sir, what will happen\Nto France now without you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382075,389249}Victor. There is no shame in executing orders\Nissued by an incompetent government.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.83,0:06:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:389833,393295}Soldiers must obey\Nthe orders they're given.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.29,0:06:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393295,399217}Even if the order is wrong, the military\Nmust comply with it and fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:446640,452229}In this war, thousands\Nof soldiers gave their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.22,0:07:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:452229,458485}Perhaps death on the battlefield\Nwas their destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.48,0:07:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:458485,462906}But when you look\Nat each of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:462906,468120}when you take their uniforms off,\Nyou'll see a loving man in each.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.12,0:07:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:468120,473834}Each of them had someone they loved:\Nparents, children, siblings, a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.83,0:07:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:473834,476461}Still, they left them\Nand went to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.14,0:08:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:488140,490142}The fate of their homeland\Nafter their death
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.14,0:08:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:490142,492978}is the only small reward\Nthey get for their efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.97,0:08:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:492978,498984}However, when their death\Nonly serves the interests of Thiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.98,0:08:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:498984,503989}I can't be called anything but\Na traitor who has betrayed their trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:503989,507367}My resignation\Nis the only right choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:507367,511955}It is also compensation\Nfor those who died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.95,0:08:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:511955,514958}How about you, Captain Langlois?\NWhat will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.95,0:08:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:514958,517002}I am a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.00,0:08:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:517002,522174}No matter what the order is,\Nthe soldier must carry it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.17,0:08:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:522174,527721}It is not my role to decide\Nwhether the order is correct or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.72,0:08:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:527721,530807}You yourself said so just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.80,0:08:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:530807,534102}I understand.\NThat, too, is a way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.10,0:08:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534102,536771}So this is where our paths part,\NCaptain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.77,0:08:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:536771,539649}Remember to always\Nvalue your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.87,0:09:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:554873,558502}{\i1}It's the only way I know to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.50,0:09:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:558502,560504}{\i1}That's who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.42,0:09:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:563423,570138}{\i1}The next day, Victor\Nhappened to see a wanted poster.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:570138,574100}{\i1}In it, there was Isabelle's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:589407,593954}Hey, Jean, have you noticed\Nwe're not moving at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.07,0:09:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:594079,598792}There's nothing we can do about it.\NThere's no wind. Take a sit and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.79,0:10:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:598792,602379}Quit raving about it!\NSooner or later it'll blow and we'll sail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.29,0:10:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603296,606007}Boy, you sure are reckless, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.00,0:10:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:606007,610220}I need to deliver this letter\Nas soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.88,0:10:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:610887,612847}I was waiting for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:612847,614307}For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.30,0:10:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:614307,617852}To see your anger.\NYou're so beautiful when you're mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.85,0:10:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:617852,621606}And this short cut?\NIt suits you perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:621606,623858}I think I've fallen\Nfor you all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.85,0:10:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:623858,626653}Real funny, Jean.\NI've had enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.65,0:10:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:626653,629948}You've got some nerve to joke around\Nunder such circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.49,0:10:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:630490,634536}This situation is the\Nperfect time to joke around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.53,0:10:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:634536,637831}You can't control the wheel of fortune,\Nonly your attitude towards it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.83,0:10:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:637831,639958}You are so—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.95,0:10:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:639958,641918}Oh! It's a ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.91,0:10:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:641918,645088}– Look, a ship!\N– I told you so! Ahoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.08,0:10:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:645088,650385}It's a British flag! They must be coming home\Nfrom France. They can take us on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.38,0:10:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:650385,655765}– Ahoy! We need help!\N– We're here! – Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.76,0:10:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:655765,657726}Hooray, they noticed us!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:10:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:657726,659853}They did!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.85,0:11:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:659853,662480}– We're saved!\N– Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.07,0:11:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:674075,676036}Something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.03,0:11:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:676036,678163}Isabelle, can you swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.53,0:11:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679539,681249}Can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.34,0:11:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:690342,691801}Jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.83,0:12:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:720830,723541}What on earth\Nis wrong with this ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.54,0:12:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:723541,726252}Don't know but, something's\Ndefinitely wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.09,0:12:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:733093,734552}He got me good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.63,0:12:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:735637,737013}Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.01,0:12:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:737013,738306}Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.73,0:12:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:748733,749943}It's him again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.94,0:12:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:749943,753405}Are you kidding me!?\NSo much for the ship…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.57,0:12:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757575,760662}No, it's too early to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.83,0:12:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:765834,767627}You monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.29,0:12:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769295,770672}Catch me if you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.76,0:13:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:777762,780140}We meet again,\NMr. Petty Officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.84,0:13:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:819846,821973}Run, Isabelle! Run away!
Comment: 0,0:13:53.81,0:13:53.81,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:833818,833818}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.65,0:14:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:840658,843453}Isabelle, behind you!\NClimb that ladder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.12,0:14:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:844120,846039}Climb it!\NGo up, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.54,0:14:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:851544,853797}What should I do?!\NOh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.84,0:14:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:864849,867352}Hang in there, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.65,0:14:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:878655,881157}Almost there, Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.53,0:14:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:887539,889833}– Isabelle! I'm coming to you!\N– Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.34,0:15:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:900343,901761}Isabelle, jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.73,0:15:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:920738,922115}We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.49,0:15:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:922490,924242}We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.24,0:15:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:924242,925910}Hooray!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.91,0:15:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:925910,928121}Jean!\NYou were wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.33,0:15:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:929330,931875}Hey, Isabelle.\NHere, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.87,0:15:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:931875,935044}No. One must suffice.\NYou're so greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.42,0:15:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:936421,938423}She likes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.23,0:16:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:958234,964032}{\i1}Soon gulls appeared in the sky,\Na sign that they were approaching land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:964032,968119}{\i1}The crew's eyes\Nlaid on jagged cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.11,0:16:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:968119,972874}{\i1}Isabelle and Jean saw\Nthe British soil for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.16,0:16:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:976169,977128}Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:977128,978588}Hm? Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.34,0:16:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:980340,981716}How do I look?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.30,0:16:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:983301,984844}So? How do I look?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.51,0:16:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:986512,990350}Just perfect! You look good\Nin everything, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.47,0:16:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:991476,992727}Thank you, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.52,0:16:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:999525,1001027}You've changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.02,0:16:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1001027,1004864}You really think so?\NYes, I guess I have, a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004864,1008660}They say there's no progress\Nwithout change.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1009869,1015375}But I don't get you, Jean.\NWhy are you chasing after me so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.37,0:17:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1015375,1022256}I'm a terrible tomboy. Apart from\Nstrength, I have no good points.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.25,0:17:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1022256,1025510}I've never had anyone but you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.59,0:17:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1030598,1034602}I'd always been\Nweak, shy and timid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.60,0:17:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1034602,1036604}You always had had to\Nsave me from trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.27,0:17:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1038272,1043069}You were my\Nonly friend back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.06,0:17:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1043069,1045822}I knew that\NI never wanted to lose you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.36,0:17:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1047365,1051160}Fencing… Shooting…\NHorse riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.16,0:17:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051160,1053371}I learned it all because\NI was interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.70,0:17:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1054706,1057959}That's… just who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.37,0:17:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1060378,1062755}{\i1}Isabelle, you'll be my bride!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.38,0:17:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1064382,1066676}{\i1}Who'd want to marry\Nsuch a weakling?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.76,0:17:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1067760,1070054}{\i1}I am not a weakling!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.05,0:17:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1073057,1074684}{\i1}Learn to respect a lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1086029,1088865}But… you see, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.24,0:18:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1089240,1091242}I know already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.03,0:18:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1092035,1095163}Just as I've adored you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.16,0:18:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1095163,1098875}you've hated me\Nall this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.33,0:18:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1100334,1104589}It's not easy to change the feelings\Nwe've had since childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1104589,1107592}But I will make you\Nfall in love with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.88,0:18:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1109886,1111763}Some day. You will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.84,0:18:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1112847,1115099}Jean…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.60,0:18:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1115600,1118978}Because if I don't,\NI'll be very, very sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.97,0:18:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1118978,1120772}Sniff… Just kidding, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.77,0:18:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1120772,1122857}I know all too well\Nthat tears don't work on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.94,0:18:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1124942,1128946}Jean, why do you always joke\Nand belittle yourself so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.94,0:18:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1128946,1134535}It's just that if I don't do that,\NI think I'd die from embarrassment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.99,0:18:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1134994,1137413}Sorry if I interrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.20,0:19:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138206,1143377}We will reach the Dover shore soon.\NWe have prepared a boat for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.71,0:19:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1143711,1144712}A boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.71,0:19:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1144712,1147090}You are illegal immigrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.09,0:19:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1147090,1148758}Illegal?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.96,0:19:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148966,1154305}Yes. But if you steal this boat and disappear,\Nthere's nothing we can do, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.13,0:19:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1155139,1156641}Mister…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.64,0:19:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1156641,1157809}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.81,0:19:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1160812,1162480}Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.48,0:19:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1162480,1163981}Sail safely!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.82,0:19:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1168820,1170238}Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.23,0:19:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1170238,1172698}– Goodbye!\N– Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.54,0:19:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1188548,1192343}So, young lady, you're about to\Ntake your first step on the British soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.34,0:19:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1192343,1194345}Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.54,0:20:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1222540,1227378}{\i1}The night after Isabelle\Nand Jean landed in England,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1227378,1231299}{\i1}they reached\Ntheir destination: London.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1232216,1235761}Let's look… SE9, SE10.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.76,0:20:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1235761,1237013}Are you sure of this address?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.01,0:20:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1237013,1240808}Yes, I am.\NDomino Street, SE17.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.80,0:20:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1240808,1244061}Over there is 12, there 13…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.44,0:20:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1248441,1251402}Two lads. Two lads!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.40,0:20:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1251402,1254280}Look carefully.\NOne of them may be in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.78,0:20:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1254780,1257992}They both look like\Nplain boys to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.40,0:21:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1258409,1260828}– Watch their every move.\N– Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.41,0:21:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1264415,1266292}– We're here.\N– Awesome. Let's knock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1266292,1267627}Just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1271005,1271964}It'll take a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.96,0:21:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1271964,1273591}Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.59,0:21:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1274592,1277136}He took out a compact!\NIt's a girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.09,0:21:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278095,1280264}Just like I suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.26,0:21:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1280264,1281974}Very well. Shoot them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.60,0:21:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1286604,1287772}Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.77,0:21:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1287772,1289857}I won't let you hurt her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1289857,1291692}Gaston?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.69,0:21:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1291692,1294862}Look, it's our\Nwould-be dead man.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.86,0:21:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1294862,1298282}Thanks for saving me the effort\Nof searching for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.28,0:21:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1298282,1302286}Let me deal with you before\NI take care of the girl. Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.28,0:21:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1302286,1302954}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.12,0:21:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307124,1308668}What a vigorous old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.96,0:21:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1314966,1316884}There is nowhere to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.80,0:22:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1322807,1325685}Panza! Welcome to London.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.89,0:22:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1326894,1328980}Who are you, you rubes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.98,0:22:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328980,1331565}I am Count Red,\Nand this is my shadow army.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.69,0:22:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332692,1334360}Count Red?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.65,0:22:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1335653,1340032}Panza. I suggest you\Nto retreat voluntarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.70,0:22:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1348708,1350459}{\i1}Where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.63,0:22:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1354630,1357633}Count Red?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.96,0:22:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1359969,1362096}What do you want?\NIt's the middle of the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.43,0:22:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1364432,1367977}Does someone by the name\Nof Martin Schmidt live here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.97,0:22:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1367977,1370354}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.10,0:22:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1369103,1371856}{\an8}Mom, where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.35,0:22:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1370354,1374317}Quiet! If you eat everything,\Nyour butt is doomed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.65,0:22:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1375651,1379572}We were sent by Jules from Paris.\NWhere can we find Mr. Schmidt?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.57,0:23:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1379572,1381949}Knowing him, he's\Nguzzling beer in a pub again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.94,0:23:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1381949,1382658}In a pub?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.65,0:23:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1382658,1387038}His favorite is called "Max In".\NMake sure to check there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.87,0:23:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1394879,1399342}{\i1}At that time, London was a refuge\Nfor revolutionaries, thinkers,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.34,0:23:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1399342,1403971}{\i1}and tramps looking for a way\Nto earn some extra money.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.97,0:23:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1403971,1410269}{\i1}These people spent their free time\Ngathering and hanging out in pubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.26,0:23:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1410269,1413898}{\i1}Max In was one of those pubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.15,0:23:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1421155,1427286}{\i1}Isabelle felt a strange emotion\Nshe had never experienced before,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.28,0:23:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1427286,1429580}{\i1}as she stood shocked,\Nin this alien environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.70,0:23:57.54,Credits,[credits],0,0,0,,{TIME:1432708,1437546}{\fad(400,200)\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.7\fs17\an5\pos(511,371)\t(4338,4838,5,\c&H101010&)}To be continued
Comment: 0,0:23:58.42,0:23:58.42,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1438422,1438422}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.42,0:24:00.59,Default,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:1438422,1440591}Next episode preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.09,0:24:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1441092,1445930}We arrived in the city of fog, London,\Nand we got to meet Mr. Schmidt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.93,0:24:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1445930,1449225}Panza, however,\Ngives us no peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.22,0:24:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1449225,1453521}Then suddenly\NVictor makes his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.52,0:24:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1453521,1455773}Next time on "Isabelle from Paris":
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.77,0:24:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1455773,1458317}"Love Burning in The Night Fog".\NPlease look forward to it.
Comment: 0,0:24:18.31,0:24:18.31,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1458317,1458317}Ending
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.37,0:24:44.38,ED JP,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1478379,1484385}{\blur0.5}anata no egao wa\Ntotemo suteki
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.38,0:24:49.84,ED JP,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1484385,1489849}{\blur0.5}soyokaze no you ni\Natatakai ai ga aru
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.84,0:24:54.81,ED JP,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1489849,1494812}{\blur0.5}RANRARA hazunda uta wa\Nogawa wo koete
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.81,0:25:00.06,ED JP,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1494812,1500067}{\blur0.5}midori no yama ni\Nkodama suru
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.06,0:25:05.44,ED JP,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1500067,1505447}{\blur0.5}hora omoikiri\Nkakete yukou
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.44,0:25:11.37,ED JP,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1505447,1511370}{\blur0.5}ano hito no iru\Noka no ue made
